 # Project Name
 
+## Description
+
+This project is a file watcher and patch management system.
+
+## Usage
+
+1. Run `npm install` to install the required dependencies.
+2. Configure the environment variables or command line arguments as needed.
+3. Run `npm start` to start the application.
+
+## Configuration Options
+
+The following options can be configured via environment variables or command line arguments:
+
+- `PROJECT_FOLDER_PATH`: The path to the project folder where CCA will scan for changes.
+- `PATCH_FILE_NAME`: The file name for the generated patch file that CCA will use to apply changes each time file changes are detected.
+- `PATCH_FILE_PATH`: The path to the .patch file that will be used by CCA to apply project changes.
+- `OUTPUT_FILE_NAME`: The file name for the generated response file that CCA will overwrite each time project changes are detected.
+- `OUTPUT_FILE_PATH`: The target path for the generated response file.
+- `IGNORED_FILES`: Used to provide additional file names to ignore during project watch.
+- `IGNORED_DIRECTORIES`: Used to provide additional file directory names to ignore during project watch.
+
+Please ensure that your project is up to date with the latest changes and configurations.
+
